<topic id="UsingSceneModes-8E8CDDD8" xml:lang="en">
<title>Using Scene Modes</title>
<shortdesc>With scene modes, the camera still performs most functions
automatically, but you exercise more control by describing the shooting
environment to the camera. Examples of scene modes include night portrait,
beach and snow, and sports.</shortdesc>
<prolog>
<metadata><keywords><indexterm>scene modes</indexterm><indexterm>modes,
scene</indexterm></keywords></metadata>
</prolog>
<body>
<p>To use one of the scene modes:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Rotate the Mode dial to SCN</p></li>
<li><p>Press the Menu button to view the first scene mode.</p></li>
<li><p>Rotate the main dial to scan through all the scene modes. Keep
rotating until you find the one you want.<fn>If you rotate past the
last scene mode, the first scene mode is displayed.</fn></p></li><?Pub
Caret 180?>
<li><p>Press the Set button to select the displayed scene mode.</p
></li>
<li><p>Use the camera like a point and shoot camera.</p></li>
</ol>
</body>
</topic>
